{
  "stem": "23730.4",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[BEEP]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we were marched from Wustegiersdorf into the Silesian Mountains and hills-- 1,000 people.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "After a couple of days, half of the column of the group was taken to Flossenburg concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I remember looking down.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We went up a kind of serpentine road, yes?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And  we looked down.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we saw the other half going left, taking that turn.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I waved to [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I waved to him.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And he waved back-- the man who gave me the little food the last moment.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they went to Flossenberg.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "After the war, he told me-- [?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Levy ?] survived the war.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "He told me the journey to Flossenberg was absolutely indescribable.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "They ate each other.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They were 120 people pushed into-- it-- he couldn't even start describing it.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "That was the half of us going to Flossenburg.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "We were marched over the the hills  and mountain of Silesia day after day.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "But by that time, I made friends with  a German guard, Helmut, who was always trying to be near my side, walking near to me.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I spoke German.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "He was a lovely chap.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "He gave me some food sometimes [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] by that time.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And we were marched and marched.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And then we ended up-- the weather became impossible.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "It was winter-- snow and ice.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And it was-- deteriorated so much that we  had to stop and put into different, different farms.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And we ended up on a farm on the left.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "There was a big farm, a Max was looking, a man in his late '60s.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "You know, [? this ?] [? big ?] man in the Wellington boots looking at us.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "Eventually, we were put into a barn, to a barn-- 200 of us-- no windows, no nothing.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "But we heard him pleading.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
